  <text>
      <body>
        
     
      <div xml:id="Sonnet41"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="sonnet"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="happy"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="society"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
               <l>O, ever skilled to wear the form we love!</l>
               <l>To bid the shapes of fear and grief depart;</l> 
               <l>Come, gentle Hope! with one gay smile remove</l>
               <l>The lasting sadness of an aching heart.</l>
               <l>Thy voice, benign Enchantress! let me hear;</l>
               <l>Say that for me some pleasures yet shall bloom,</l>
               <l>That Fancy's radiance, Friendship's precious tear,</l>
               <l>Shall soften, or shall chase, misfortune's gloom.</l>
               <l>But come not glowing in the dazzling ray,</l>
               <l>Which once with dear illusions charm'd my eye,</l>
               <l>O! strew no more, sweet flatterer! on my way</l>
               <l>The flowers I fondly thought too bright to die;</l>
               <l>visions less fair will soothe my pensive breast,</l>
               <l>That asks not happiness, but longs for rest! </l>
               
